Here are the three rationalized forms.  In each case we multiply top and bottom by a suitable cube‐root so that the new denominator becomes a perfect cube.

a)  
\[
\frac1{\sqrt[3]{11}}
\;\times\;
\frac{\sqrt[3]{11^2}}{\sqrt[3]{11^2}}
\;=\;
\frac{\sqrt[3]{11^2}}{\sqrt[3]{11^3}}
\;=\;
\frac{\sqrt[3]{121}}{11}.
\]

b)  
\[
\sqrt[3]{\frac7{54}}
\;=\;
\frac{\sqrt[3]7}{\sqrt[3]{54}}
\;=\;
\frac{\sqrt[3]7}{\sqrt[3]{27\cdot2}}
\;=\;
\frac{\sqrt[3]7}{3\,\sqrt[3]2}
\;\times\;
\frac{\sqrt[3]{2^2}}{\sqrt[3]{2^2}}
\;=\;
\frac{\sqrt[3]{7\cdot4}}{3\sqrt[3]{2^3}}
\;=\;
\frac{\sqrt[3]{28}}{3\cdot2}
\;=\;
\frac{\sqrt[3]{28}}6.
\]

c)  
\[
\frac{3}{\sqrt[3]{3x^2}}
\;\times\;
\frac{\sqrt[3]{(3x^2)^2}}{\sqrt[3]{(3x^2)^2}}
\;=\;
\frac{3\,\sqrt[3]{9x^4}}{\sqrt[3]{27x^6}}
\;=\;
\frac{3\,\sqrt[3]{9x^4}}{3x^2}
\;=\;
\frac{\sqrt[3]{9x^4}}{x^2}.
\]
One often factors \(9x^4= x^3\cdot(9x)\) inside the cube–root to get the slightly more compact
\[
\frac{\sqrt[3]{9x^4}}{x^2}
\;=\;
\frac{x\,\sqrt[3]{9x}}{x^2}
\;=\;
\frac{\sqrt[3]{9x}}{x}.
\]

To rationalize the denominator, multiply top and bottom by the conjugate of \(2-\sqrt6\), namely \(2+\sqrt6\):

\[
\frac{7}{2-\sqrt6}
\;\times\;
\frac{2+\sqrt6}{2+\sqrt6}
\;=\;
\frac{7(2+\sqrt6)}{(2-\sqrt6)(2+\sqrt6)}
\;=\;
\frac{7(2+\sqrt6)}{2^2 - (\sqrt6)^2}
\;=\;
\frac{7(2+\sqrt6)}{4 - 6}
\;=\;
\frac{7(2+\sqrt6)}{-2}
\;=\;
-\frac{7(2+\sqrt6)}{2}.
\]

You can leave it as
\[
-\frac{7(2+\sqrt6)}{2},
\]
or distribute:
\[
-\frac{14 + 7\sqrt6}{2}
\;=\;
-7 \;-\;\frac{7\sqrt6}{2}.
\]
